}

}
public int pop(){
if(isEmpty())

}

questiontext.text:
De klasse Seq heeft de volgende API:

  • boolean isEmpty() - Returns true if and only if the list contains no elements
  • Object head() - returns the first element of the sequence. It is an error to call first() on an empty sequence.
  • Seq tail() - returns a list that consists of all elements of the sequence, except its first one. It is an error to call tail() on an empty sequence.
  • Seq add(Object o) - returns a sequence that starts with o and contains all elements of this sequence
  • Voor iedere niet-lege sequence  seq geldt seq.tail().add(seq.head).equals(seq);

Waarom werkt de volgende recursieve methode niet?

public int count(Seq s) {
  int c = count(s.tail());
  if ( s.tail().isEmpty() ) {
    return 1; // This is a one, not an ell!
  } else {
    return c++;
  }
}

public int driehoek(int n) {

if (n==0) return 0;

else return (driehoek(n-1) - n);

}

if (n==0) return 0;

}

else return (n-1 + driehoek(n));

}

else return (n + driehoek(n-1));

}
